articles.author: Lee Ying Shan
articles.title: Japan stocks extend post-election rally with Nikkei 225 breaching 58,000 for the first time - CNBC
articles.description: Other markets in Asia also shrugged off strong U.S. payrolls data that has dampened expectations for Federal Reserve rate cuts and sent Wall Street lower overnight.
articles.content: Japan's Nikkei 225 on Thursday hit 58,000 for the first time in history, extending its post-election rally to fresh highs, fueled by renewed confidence in domestic politics and the ruling administrat… [+2211 chars]
